    {
      "id": "method1-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 650,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 25,
      "text": "METHOD 1: D555 / Misura Scanner (Primary)",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "strokeColor": "#c92a2a",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "seed": 48,
      "groupIds": [
        "method1"
      ],
      "boundElements": [],
      "locked": false,
      "roundness": null,
      "link": null,
      "updated": 1778490732387,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1221495889,
      "index": "al",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "frameId": null,
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "METHOD 1: D555 / Misura Scanner (Primary)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.5625
    },
    {
      "id": "method1-desc",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 680,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 230,
      "text": "Hardware: D555 depth camera + Misura software\nAPI: Local server (ngrok) → measurement-proxy edge fn\n\nFlow on 80% Display (DisplayCaptureFlow):\n  1. Health check → /health (is D555 connected?)\n  2. If healthy:\n     a. Front instruction video (7s)\n     b. capture-front API → D555 captures RGB+depth (front)\n     c. Hold still countdown (3s)\n     d. Side instruction video (7s)\n     e. capture-side API → D555 captures RGB+depth (side)\n     f. Hold still countdown (3s)\n     g. get-dimensions API → D555 processes both views\n  3. measurement-proxy converts cm → inches\n  4. Detects gender via Gemini (customer_profile)\n  5. Computes recommended sizes (top S/M/L, trouser 28/30..)\n  6. Saves body_measurements to vto_sessions DB\n  7. Broadcasts MEASUREMENTS_READY to tablet",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "seed": 49,
      "groupIds": [
        "method1"
      ],
      "boundElements": [],
      "locked": false,
      "roundness": null,
      "link": null,
      "updated": 1778490732387,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1517018431,
      "index": "am",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "frameId": null,
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Hardware: D555 depth camera + Misura software\nAPI: Local server (ngrok) → measurement-proxy edge fn\n\nFlow on 80% Display (DisplayCaptureFlow):\n  1. Health check → /health (is D555 connected?)\n  2. If healthy:\n     a. Front instruction video (7s)\n     b. capture-front API → D555 captures RGB+depth (front)\n     c. Hold still countdown (3s)\n     d. Side instruction video (7s)\n     e. capture-side API → D555 captures RGB+depth (side)\n     f. Hold still countdown (3s)\n     g. get-dimensions API → D555 processes both views\n  3. measurement-proxy converts cm → inches\n  4. Detects gender via Gemini (customer_profile)\n  5. Computes recommended sizes (top S/M/L, trouser 28/30..)\n  6. Saves body_measurements to vto_sessions DB\n  7. Broadcasts MEASUREMENTS_READY to tablet",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.1616161616161618
    },
    {
