    {
      "id": "method3-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1080,
      "y": 650,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 25,
      "text": "METHOD 3: Client-Side MediaPipe + Heuristics",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "strokeColor": "#495057",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "seed": 54,
      "groupIds": [
        "method3"
      ],
      "boundElements": [],
      "locked": false,
      "roundness": null,
      "link": null,
      "updated": 1778490732387,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 394052081,
      "index": "ar",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "frameId": null,
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "METHOD 3: Client-Side MediaPipe + Heuristics",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.5625
    },
    {
      "id": "method3-desc",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1080,
      "y": 680,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 230,
      "text": "File: use-body-measurements.js (client-side)\nAI: MediaPipe Pose Detection (CDN loaded)\n\nUsed as last-resort fallback in browser:\n\nFlow:\n  1. Load MediaPipe Pose model from CDN\n  2. Detect 33 body landmarks from full-body image:\n     NOSE, SHOULDERS, ELBOWS, WRISTS,\n     HIPS, KNEES, ANKLES\n  3. Calculate pixel distances between landmarks\n  4. Convert px → cm using known height ratio\n  5. Derive measurements:\n     - Shoulder width = shoulder-to-shoulder distance\n     - Chest = shoulder width × 2.4\n     - Waist = hip width × 2.2\n     - Arm/sleeve/torso/inseam from landmark chains\n  6. Apply size recommendation algorithm\n\nFinal fallback: estimateFromHeuristics()\n  Uses body proportion ratios (e.g., waist = 44% height)",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "seed": 55,
      "groupIds": [
        "method3"
      ],
      "boundElements": [],
      "locked": false,
      "roundness": null,
      "link": null,
      "updated": 1778490732387,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1025331615,
      "index": "as",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "frameId": null,
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "File: use-body-measurements.js (client-side)\nAI: MediaPipe Pose Detection (CDN loaded)\n\nUsed as last-resort fallback in browser:\n\nFlow:\n  1. Load MediaPipe Pose model from CDN\n  2. Detect 33 body landmarks from full-body image:\n     NOSE, SHOULDERS, ELBOWS, WRISTS,\n     HIPS, KNEES, ANKLES\n  3. Calculate pixel distances between landmarks\n  4. Convert px → cm using known height ratio\n  5. Derive measurements:\n     - Shoulder width = shoulder-to-shoulder distance\n     - Chest = shoulder width × 2.4\n     - Waist = hip width × 2.2\n     - Arm/sleeve/torso/inseam from landmark chains\n  6. Apply size recommendation algorithm\n\nFinal fallback: estimateFromHeuristics()\n  Uses body proportion ratios (e.g., waist = 44% height)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 0.9956709956709957
    },
